# Main process conventions

## Layering

```
routes/  →  controller/  →  models/ | base/
```

- **routes/** — IPC handlers only: parse `request.packet.body`, call controller, `request.send(status, body)`
- **controller/** — business logic, no direct IPC calls
- **base/** — singleton services (`task-tracker`, `authentication`, `offline-mode`, `api`)
- **models/** — Sequelize definitions; schema changes need a new file in `migrations/`

## IPC

Use `@amazingcat/electron-ipc-router` with `namespace/action` route names:

```javascript
router.serve('tasks/list', async request => { /* ... */ });
```

Register new route files in [app/src/routes/index.js](app/src/routes/index.js).

## Error handling

```javascript
const { UIError } = require('../utils/errors');

// Expected user-facing errors → pass through
if (error instanceof UIError)
  return request.send(error.code, { message: error.message, id: error.errorId, error: error.error });

// Unexpected → log and return 500 with error id
log.error('...', error);
request.send(500, { message: 'Internal error occured', id: 'ERxxx500' });
```

## Logging

```javascript
const Logger = require('../utils/log');
const log = new Logger('ModuleName');
```

## Sequelize

- Access models via `require('../models').db.models`
- Strip Sequelize metadata before IPC response (see `purifyInstances` in routes/tasks.js)
- New migration: timestamped file in `migrations/`, run automatically on startup via Umzug

## API

- Cattr server client: [app/src/base/api.js](app/src/base/api.js) (`@cattr/node` + keychain providers)
- Config paths and feature flags: [app/src/base/config.js](app/src/base/config.js)
